As mentioned by @kkmann in #23, we need to consider how dependencies of an installed package might need to be handled.

@kkmann had suggested that, at least initially, we allow all locally installed packages to share a library.

I think that this will work for fairly established packages that are well maintained, but will cause issues when we introduce packages with strictly conflicting package dependencies. I don't think this is a problem we should consider in-scope for now, and would be onboard to move forward with a shared library.

